Hey guys! I teamed up with @amika to share my go to holiday looks using my favorite Amika products whenever I am in a rush and my hair is dirty! All the products shown in the video are available at Sephora.
ü¶ãStep 1: Blockade Heat Defense Serum |I always start with a heat protectant whenever using heat styling tools to protect my hair. This lightweight serum not only provides protection but also smooths, moisturizes the ends and adds shine.
ü¶ãStep 2: Jack of all Curls set | Today I will be using the 25mm barrel with an interchangeable curler to achieve big/voluminous curls. What I love about this kit is that it features five rose gold, ceramic barrels that stores neatly and is easy to travel with since it comes in a custom carrying case. The interchangeable barrels heat up quickly and provides adjustable temperature control from 250-450F (120-230C). This type of hair style works the best with second/third day hair because it gives the hair a grip to hold the curls. If you have really silky or your hair just doesn‚Äôt hold curls, I recommend sparing flexible hair spray before wrapping the hair on a barrel. When wrapping the hair, I usually grab an inch and only wrap away from my face, hold for 5-6 secs and release. Be sure to let the curls cool before touching them!
ü¶ãStep 3: Perk Up Dry Shampoo | It is a talc free dry shampoo that absorbs and refreshes hair with natural rice starch. What is rice starch? It is a light powder that absorbs dirt/oil while adding volume and texture to the hair. I love how this dry shampoo does not leave a white cast on my dark hair nor does it leave any sticky residue. The lightweight formula gives me the freedom to extend my style for a day or two without making my hair feel stiff or causing any irritation to the scalp. I usually blast my hair with the blowdrier first to absorb any sweat/moistness (lol) then go in with the dry shampoo and let it sit for 5-10 minutes for it to work it‚Äôs magic before massaging the product in and brushing the curls out.
